-s stars. However, the excess of C and\ns-process elements in some single CEMP-s stars was apparently transferred to\ntheir natal clouds by an external (distant) source. This finding has important\nimplications for our understanding of carbon enrichment in the early Galactic\nhalo and some high-redshift DLA systems, and of the mass loss from extremely\nmetal-poor AGB stars. Abridged.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jan 2016 20:58:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-23"}
