iable on\ntime-average and significantly alters the global heat budget in the convective\nregime. Our results suggest, that the boundary forcing not only introduces a\nnet horizontal heat transport but also suppresses the convection locally to\nsuch an extent, that the net Nusselt number is reduced by up to 50\\%, even\nthough the mean CMB heat flux is conserved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jan 2016 15:07:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-26"}
